`crates/` is the workspace root holding six independent, standalone crates that together implement a `.context/`-based documentation and sandboxing toolchain: scanning/summarizing a repo into rollup/leaf `.ctx` files, serving that chain to agents, verifying and briefing around it, and sandboxing the agent process itself. There is no shared library code here — each crate is its own binary/CLI with its own Cargo.toml, and cross-crate dependency is narrow and explicit rather than pervasive.

The dependency chain runs `ctx-core` → `ctx-scan`/`ctx-context` (both depend on ctx-core's path-safety and hash-sidecar schema) and `ctx-scan` → `ctx-summarize` (wraps its `Fs`/`Agent` traits). `ctx-verify` and `ctx-brief` sit downstream as operational tooling around the same `.context/` conventions but without direct code dependency. `ctx-cage` is fully separate — a sandboxing crate with no relation to the `.ctx` pipeline — bundled here only because it's part of the same workspace.

The invariant every crate in this pipeline restates independently rather than sharing: the `.context/` mirror layout, rollup/leaf naming, and freshness markers are each asserted in-crate (schema in ctx-core, walker/reconcile in ctx-scan, chain rendering in ctx-context) with no single source of truth enforcing consistency across crate boundaries — a change to the on-disk convention in one crate does not propagate compiler-checked to the others.

No `intent.md` exists at this level, so no divergence check applies.